    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style identified retroactively to describe works of the late 17th and 18th centuries. Considered a modification of the Baroque, and often appearing in autocratic monarchies of France and Britain, where the original excesses of the Baroque are lessened and elements of classical antiquity are re-established.</Note_Text>
